{"type":"message","id":"157b3c06","parentId":"a333a0b7","timestamp":"2026-03-23T21:51:27.435Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_a4lioy1ww2g1_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 4799\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=1864\r\n[mutation parse failed] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=1864\r\n[master e533a11] pulse: 2026-03-23 175104\n 6 files changed, 262 insertions(+), 120 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-23 175104.md\n rename mutations/{proposed => rejected}/2026-03-23 174102.mutation (100%)\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-23 175104 - The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment requires analyzing pulse log files to identify invariant patterns that repeat across sessions. A classifier script is needed to measure invariant/variant classification accuracy and test next-pulse prediction.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"quick-pine","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 4799\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=1864\r\n[mutation parse failed] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=1864\r\n[master e533a11] pulse: 2026-03-23 175104\n 6 files changed, 262 insertions(+), 120 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-23 175104.md\n rename mutations/{proposed => rejected}/2026-03-23 174102.mutation (100%)\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-23 175104 - The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment requires analyzing pulse log files to identify invariant patterns that repeat across sessions. A classifier script is needed to measure invariant/variant classification accuracy and test next-pulse prediction.\r\n","name":"pwsh C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774302687433}}
{"type":"message","id":"212921bb","parentId":"157b3c06","timestamp":"2026-03-23T21:51:31.370Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, the pulse script ran. Now let me read the most recent log file to get the details.","thinkingSignature":"6f8bd23df980100555a5eba09c53a788381a95afd01d00d3555ac3c7b9461407"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_z7jacmbfpf62_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\pulse_2026-03-23 174102.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":722,"output":74,"cacheRead":11887,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":12683,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774302687436}}
{"type":"message","id":"f381d64d","parentId":"212921bb","timestamp":"2026-03-23T21:51:31.381Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_z7jacmbfpf62_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-23 174102\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: experiments/TIC-EXPERIMENT.md (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLooking at the current state, I need to advance Phase 1 with the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment. The pending action is:\r\n\r\n\"Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\"\r\n\r\nThis is a concrete file edit that advances the goals. I should:\r\n1. Create a TIC classifier script\r\n2. Apply it to the pulse logs\r\n3. Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n\r\nThe key insight is that causal structure = invariant structure, and compression discovers invariants. So I need to:\r\n- Read the pulse log files\r\n- Extract patterns that repeat vs change\r\n- Classify content as invariant (causal) or variant\r\n- Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n\r\nLet me create a practical TIC implementation script that can be run on the existing pulse logs.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC experiment requires a classifier that can distinguish invariant (causally significant) vs variant content across pulse logs. A Python script processing the existing pulse_*.md files is the most direct path to validating the Compression-Causal Duality hypothesis.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `tic/classifier.py` - a Temporal Invariance Compression classifier that analyzes pulse logs to identify repeating structures (invariants) vs unique content (variants), then predicts next-pulse content from learned invariants.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n`\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTemporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\nTests hypothesis: causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n\r\nTIC finds patterns that repeat across sessions (invariants) which \r\nrepresent causal relationships, vs patterns that change (variants).\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport re\r\nimport os\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\nimport json\r\n\r\nLOG_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nMIN_VARIANT_FREQ = 1\r\nMIN_INVARIANT_FREQ = 2\r\n\r\nclass TICClassifier:\r\n    def __init__(self):\r\n        self.invariants = Counter()  # Patterns that repeat\r\n        self.variants = Counter()    # Patterns that appear once\r\n        self.pulse_content = []      # Raw pulse content\r\n        \r\n    def extract_tokens(self, text):\r\n        \"\"\"Extract meaningful tokens from pulse text.\"\"\"\r\n        # Section headers, goals, file references\r\n        tokens = []\r\n        # Goal patterns: - [ ] task or - [x] completed\r\n        tokens.extend(re.findall(r'-\\s*\\[[ x]\\]\\s*([^\\n]+)', text))\r\n        # Section headers\r\n        tokens.extend(re.findall(r'^##?\\s+([^\\n]+)', text, re.MULTILINE))\r\n        # File paths\r\n        tokens.extend(re.findall(r'`([^`]+)`', text))\r\n        tokens.extend(re.findall(r'(\\w+\\.\\w+)', text))\r\n        return [t.strip().lower() for t in tokens if t.strip()]\r\n    \r\n    def classify_content(self, all_pulses):\r\n        \"\"\"Classify content as invariant or variant across all pulses.\"\"\"\r\n        content_tokens = [self.extract_tokens(p) for p in all_pulses]\r\n        \r\n        # Global token frequency\r\n        global_freq = Counter()\r\n        for tokens in content_tokens:\r\n            global_freq.update(set(tokens))  # Unique tokens per pulse\r\n        \r\n        for tokens in content_tokens:\r\n            for token in tokens:\r\n                if global_freq[token] >= MIN_INVARIANT_FREQ:\r\n                    self.invariants[token] += 1\r\n                else:\r\n                    self.variants[token] += 1\r\n        \r\n        # Calculate invariant ratio\r\n        total = sum(self.invariants.values()) + sum(self.variants.values())\r\n        invariant_ratio = sum(self.invariants.values()) / total if total > 0 else 0\r\n        \r\n        return {\r\n            'invariant_count': len(self.invariants),\r\n            'variant_count': len(self.variants),\r\n            'invariant_ratio': invariant_ratio,\r\n            'top_invariants': self.invariants.most_common(10),\r\n            'top_variants': self.variants.most_common(10)\r\n        }\r\n    \r\n    def predict_next(self, current_pulse, all_pulses):\r\n        \"\"\"Predict content of next pulse based on invariants.\"\"\"\r\n        current_tokens = set(self.extract_tokens(current_pulse))\r\n        \r\n        # Find invariants that appeared recently but not in current\r\n        predicted = []\r\n        for token, freq in self.invariants.most_common(50):\r\n            if token not in current_tokens and freq >= 2:\r\n                predicted.append(token)\r\n        \r\n        return predicted[:10]  # Top 10 predictions\r\n    \r\n    def run_experiment(self):\r\n        \"\"\"Run TIC on pulse logs and report results.\"\"\"\r\n        pulse_files = sorted(LOG_DIR.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"))\r\n        print(f\"Found {len(pulse_files)} pulse logs\")\r\n        \r\n        all_pulses = []\r\n        for pf in pulse_files:\r\n            content = pf.read_text()\r\n            all_pulses.append(content)\r\n        \r\n        if len(all_pulses) < 3:\r\n            print(\"Need at least 3 pulses for meaningful experiment\")\r\n            return\r\n        \r\n        # Classify\r\n        results = self.classify_content(all_pulses)\r\n        print(f\"\\n=== TIC RESULTS ===\")\r\n        print(f\"Invariant patterns: {results['invariant_count']}\")\r\n        print(f\"Variant patterns: {results['variant_count']}\")\r\n        print(f\"Invariant ratio: {results['invariant_ratio']:.1%}\")\r\n        \r\n        print(f\"\\nTop Invariants (causal structure):\")\r\n        for token, freq in results['top_invariants'][:5]:\r\n            print(f\"  {token}: {freq}\")\r\n        \r\n        # Prediction test (use last pulse as \"current\", predict what NEXT would be)\r\n        if all_pulses:\r\n            current = all_pulses[-1]\r\n            predictions = self.predict_next(current, all_pulses)\r\n\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-23 17:41:30\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774302691379}}
